- **Service Type**: The classification of the global scheduled bus transport market according to the service type involves distinguishing between regular bus service and premium bus service. Regular bus services are oriented towards the general public, offering affordability and multiple stops along the route to cater to a broad audience. Conversely, premium bus services target customers seeking enhanced comfort, amenities, and a more direct travel experience at a premium price point.

- **Bus Type**: Another essential segmentation factor is the type of buses utilized for transport services. This segment includes rigid buses, articulated buses, and double-decker buses. Rigid buses, characterized by a single compartment, are commonly used for standard transportation needs. Articulated buses feature an additional joint in the middle, increasing passenger capacity and flexibility. Double-decker buses, with their dual levels, provide increased seating capacity and are often employed for high-traffic routes.

- **Booking Platform**: The booking platform segment identifies the various methods through which passengers can make reservations for their bus journeys. This category encompasses online booking, mobile applications, and traditional ticket counters. Online booking has gained popularity due to its convenience and accessibility, providing passengers with the flexibility to plan and purchase tickets from anywhere. Mobile applications offer additional functionalities such as real-time updates on schedules and availability, enhancing the overall booking experience. Traditional ticket counters cater to individuals who prefer a more personalized and hands-on approach to ticket purchasing.

